==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intramolecular
<hw>In`tra*mo*lec"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Chem. & Physics)</fld> <def>Between molecules; situated, or
acting, between the molecules of bodies.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Being or occurring within a single molecule; <as>as,
<ex>intramolecular</ex> hydrogen bonds</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intramundane</ent>⟦br⟧
